# API Routes

## User Routes

| Method | Endpoint                  | Description                        |
| ------ | ------------------------- | ---------------------------------- |
| GET    | /api/user/me              | Get authenticated user profile     |
| PUT    | /api/user/update          | Update authenticated user profile  |
| GET    | /api/user/student/stats   | Get student dashboard statistics   |
| GET    | /api/user/admin/analytics | Get admin analytics dashboard data |
| GET    | /api/user/list            | Get all users (admin only)         |
| PUT    | /api/user/ban/:userId     | Ban or unban a specific user       |

---

## Tutor Routes

| Method | Endpoint                        | Description                         |
| ------ | ------------------------------- | ----------------------------------- |
| GET    | /api/tutors                     | Retrieve all tutors                 |
| GET    | /api/tutors/:tutorId            | Retrieve tutor details by ID        |
| GET    | /api/tutors/overview            | Get tutor dashboard overview        |
| PUT    | /api/tutors/update              | Update tutor profile                |
| PUT    | /api/tutors/subjects            | Update tutor subjects               |
| DELETE | /api/tutors/subjects/:subjectId | Remove tutor subject                |
| PUT    | /api/tutors/feature/:tutorId    | Mark tutor as featured (admin only) |

---

## Category & Subject Routes

| Method | Endpoint                                  | Description             |
| ------ | ----------------------------------------- | ----------------------- |
| GET    | /api/categories                           | Retrieve all categories |
| POST   | /api/categories/create                    | Create new category     |
| POST   | /api/categories/subject/create            | Create new subject      |
| PUT    | /api/categories/update/:categoryId        | Update category         |
| PUT    | /api/categories/update/subject/:subjectId | Update subject          |
| DELETE | /api/categories/delete/:categoryId        | Delete category         |
| DELETE | /api/categories/delete/subject/:subjectId | Delete subject          |

---

## Availability Routes

| Method | Endpoint                                 | Description                  |
| ------ | ---------------------------------------- | ---------------------------- |
| GET    | /api/availability                        | Retrieve tutor availability  |
| POST   | /api/availability/create                 | Create availability schedule |
| PUT    | /api/availability/update/:availabilityId | Update availability schedule |
| DELETE | /api/availability/delete/:availabilityId | Delete availability schedule |

---

## Booking Routes

| Method | Endpoint                        | Description                     |
| ------ | ------------------------------- | ------------------------------- |
| GET    | /api/bookings                   | Retrieve bookings               |
| GET    | /api/bookings/:bookingId        | Retrieve booking by ID          |
| POST   | /api/bookings/create            | Create tutoring session booking |
| PUT    | /api/bookings/update/:bookingId | Update booking status           |

---

## Review Routes

| Method | Endpoint                      | Description            |
| ------ | ----------------------------- | ---------------------- |
| GET    | /api/reviews                  | Retrieve all reviews   |
| POST   | /api/reviews/create           | Create tutor review    |
| PUT    | /api/reviews/update/:reviewId | Update existing review |

---

# Booking Status Workflow

The booking system follows a structured workflow to maintain consistency and proper session management.

### CONFIRMED

This is the default status immediately after a student successfully books a tutoring session.

### COMPLETED

Tutors can mark tutoring sessions as completed after the session has finished.

### CANCELLED

Students can cancel a tutoring session before completion.

---

# File Upload System

SkillBridge uses **Multer** and **Cloudinary** for secure image uploads.

Supported image formats:

- JPG
- JPEG
- PNG
- SVG
- WEBP

Features include:

- MIME type validation
- Unique filename generation
- Cloudinary folder organization
- Automatic resource type detection

---

# Database Management

The application uses **PostgreSQL** as the primary relational database and **Prisma ORM** for database management and querying.

Prisma provides:

- Type-safe database queries
- Schema-based migrations
- Better developer experience
- Optimized query handling

---

# Installation & Setup

## 1. Clone Repository

```bash
git clone <your-repository-url>
cd skillbridge-backend
npm install
```

---

## 2. Configure Environment Variables

Create a `.env` file in the project root directory.

```env
DATABASE_URL=postgresql://username:password@localhost:5432/skillbridge

BETTER_AUTH_SECRET=your_better_auth_secret

BETTER_AUTH_URL=http://localhost:5000

CLOUDINARY_CLOUD_NAME=your_cloud_name
CLOUDINARY_API_KEY=your_api_key
CLOUDINARY_API_SECRET=your_api_secret

PORT=5000
```

---

## 3. Prisma Migration & Client Generation

```bash
npx prisma migrate dev
npx prisma generate
```

---

## 4. Start Development Server

```bash
npm run dev
```

The server will run at:

```bash
http://localhost:5000
```

